{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"912296cf-9e6d-4ae7-9cbb-eaf29454858f","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also use `DisplayName~` instead of `FullyQualifiedName~` if you prefer matching on the shorter display name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2da8d5a1-b2e4-435f-bd1e-ab5031910abc","outputTokens":157},"id":"734709d4-017a-470e-b51a-d24920818099","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:23:23.519Z","parentId":"fd27b219-444d-4289-bb0f-f82bed3ec2b0"}
